  Revert masking of PHP binary useflags.

  29 Dec 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> 1.0/use.mask,
  1.0_rc/use.mask, 1.2/use.mask, 1.4/use.mask, 2004.0/use.mask,
  2004.1/use.mask, 2004.2/use.mask, 2004.3/use.mask, 2005.0/use.mask,
  2005.1/ppc/use.mask, 2005.1/ppc64/use.mask, use.mask:
  Mask fdftk useflag on base profile and unmask for x86 only.

  16 Dec 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> +dev/ppc64/use.mask,
  +ppc64/use.mask:
  Added -ibm to use.mask on ppc64, since we're adding it to base/use.mask for
  bug #156000.

  07 Dec 2006; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> ppc32/2006.1/make.defaults:
  Added pdf as USE-flag, otherwise gtk2 will not build due to insufficient
  cairo-use-flags.

  07 Dec 2006; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org>:
  Starting with a ChangeLog as other arches already did.
